FBIS3-30092 "dreas038_d_94008" FBIS-EAS-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 South Korea Government To Allow Exchange of North Currency SK2502060894 Seoul HANGUK ILBO in Korean 25 Feb 94 p 9 SK2502060894 Seoul HANGUK ILBO Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Summary] In preparing for brisk North-South trade, the government has decided to exchange North Korea's currency that may be obtained in travel to North Korea through a third country and in trade with North Korea, at the Export-Import Bank. It was learned that on 24 February, the government has deposited 300 million won as North-South cooperation funds at the Export-Import Bank. An official of the Export-Import Bank revealed: The funds were deposited for exchange with North Korean currency in preparation for brisk North-South trade.
